11. We reply, that granting this interpretation, that these words of our Saviour have reference to Intention, (although more recent interpreters give them quite another sense,) we must distinguish two senses of Intention, It may be taken to refer to the regard had to the end only, the good at which we aim 3 as when any one is said to intend or to aim at the glory of God, or his own advantage, or his own plea- sure 3 or Intention may be taken as including the whole process, end and means together: as when any one is said to intend or to aim at the glory of Grod by building a temple, or by slaying an idolater 3 to intend or aim at his own advantage, by getting money by honest labour, or by theft and robbery.
